Five people were left injured when a taxi they were travelling in overturned on Edendale Road in Edendale, KwaZulu Natal, on Monday. ER24 spokesman, Werner Vermaak said the ER24 personnel, along with other services, arrived on the scene at 7:20am to find the taxi lying on its side in the middle of the road. “The passengers had already climbed out of the vehicle and were now found on the side of the road.Medics assessed the patients and found that all five had sustained minor to moderate injuries,” said Vermaak. “Fortunately, no serious injuries or fatalities were found on the scene.The patients were treated for their injuries and thereafter transported to nearby hospitals for further care.The driver of the taxi was not found on the scene,” he added. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigations.